## Proposed Changes

### 1. Face Recognition Service — Generalize for Both Employees & Visitors

#### [MODIFY] [face_recognition_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/CPU-compatible-AI-/apps/server/services/face_recognition_service.py)

**What changes:**
- Add `VISITORS_PHOTOS_DIR` path constant (`receptionist/photos/visitors/`)
- Add `verify_person_face(person_type, name, image_b64)` — unified entry point that routes to employee or visitor logic
- Add `verify_visitor_face(visitor_name, image_b64)`:
  - Looks up visitor by name via `get_visitor_by_name()`
  - If visitor has `id_photo_path` → compare live frame against it (same as employee flow)
  - If visitor has **no** stored photo → save the live frame as their `id_photo_path` (first-visit enrollment)
  - Return same result schema as `verify_employee_face()`
- Add `cleanup_old_captures(max_age_days=7)` — deletes files in `CAPTURES_DIR` older than N days
- Add `get_visitor_photo_path(visitor_id)` helper

**Why this design:**
- Reuses **100% of the existing DeepFace pipeline** (same model, same detector, same threshold)
- No new model loading = no additional memory
- Visitors and employees share the same result schema so the frontend doesn't need separate logic

